devdoc.details: Represents a users on-chain identity and allows to execute meta-transactions where the gas of the ethereum transaction is not payed by the owner of the identity, but a delegate. The delegate can be payed in form of a debt within a Trustlines Currency Network.*

cancelTransaction(bytes32).details: Cancels a meta-transaction by invalidating the transaction hash

params.txHash: hash of the meta-transaction to be cancelled*

changeImplementation(address).details: Changes the implementation contract if this identity uses a proxy. This allows to upgrade the functionality of a proxied identity contract to a newer protocol.     Only works, if called via a proxy contract.

params._implementation: Address of the new identity implementation contract.*

execute(address,uint256,bytes,uint256,ui.details: Executes a function in the name of this identity. Reverts if the function call fails. Can only be called by the owner of this identity.

params.data: The encoded function call to be executed at `to`
params.operationType: How to apply `data` to `to`. Valid operation types are CALL(0), DELEGATECALL(1), CREATE(2) and CREATE2(3)*
params.timeLimit: Timestamp until which this function call is allowed to be executed, afterwards it will revert
params.to: The address where to execute the function and where to send `value` coins
